<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- Pathe Communications Corp.:
   Third Payment Is Made
   In MGM/UA Acquisition
</HL>
<DATE>
05/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3
</SO>
<CO>
   PCC MGM
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)
</IN>
<LP>
   MGM/UA Communications Co. said Pathe Communications Corp.
made the third of four $50 million security deposits toward
its $1.27 billion acquisition of MGM/UA.
   Culver City, Calif.-based MGM/UA had granted Pathe an
extra week, until yesterday, to make the payment. In addition
to the $200 million in security deposits, Pathe has granted
MGM/UA a security interest of $75 million in three Pathe
films.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Pathe, a Los Angeles-based entertainment concern
controlled by Italian financier Giancarlo Parretti, launched
its $20-a-share offer for MGM/UA on March 14. It is set to
expire June 7.
</TEXT>
